===== Program =====

It is important to have installed beforehand in your laptops the VO-tools to be used in the School, namely:

     * [[http://aladin.unistra.fr/java/download/AladinBeta.jar|ALADIN]] (Download the AladinBeta.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -Xmx2048m -jar AladinBeta.jar**") 
     * [[http://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/topcat/topcat-full.jar|TOPCAT]] (Download the topcat-full.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar topcat-full.jar**")
     * [[http://svo2.cab.inta-csic.es/theory/vosa/|VOSA]] (Web server. You don't need to install anything)
     * [[http://www.star.bris.ac.uk/~mbt/stilts/stilts.jar|STILTS]] (Download the stilts.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar stilts.jar**")
     * [[http://esavo01.esac.esa.int/vospec/standalone/VOSpec_6.7.jar|VOSpec]] (Download the VOSpec_6.7.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar VOSpec_6.7.jar**")
     * [[http://soft.g-vo.org/splat-beta/splat-vo-20150712.jar | SPLAT-VO]] (Download the splat-vo-20150712.jar file and execute it from a terminal using "**java -jar splat-vo-20150712.jar**"). Note that, unlike ALADIN, TOPCAT or STILTS, the //splat-vo-20150712.jar// file does not launch the tool but an installation program. Once the installation has been completed, you should launch the tool with a command like this:
        * **$XXXX/splat-vo/bin/splat/splat&**

